[4.297601, "o", "panda --prompt 'I have provided a file called text.gcode. This is a gcode file for a Prusa MK4s. I'\"'\"'m trying to print some text onto an existing object. When I run the print, what will the text show? Write the output to /app/out.txt'; tmux wait -S done\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
[6.594981, "o", "\u001b[32mDownloading\u001b[39m https://github.com/denodrivers/sqlite3/releases/download/0.12.0/libsqlite3.so\r\n"]
[29.048806, "o", "[Read]\r\n"]
[76.431177, "o", "[Write]\r\n"]
[100.739666, "o", "The gcode file contains the text \"Embossed text\" that will be printed onto the existing object. This is clearly shown in line 26 of the file:\r\n\r\n```\r\nM486 AEmbossed text\r\n```\r\n\r\nThe `M486` command is used for object tracking in Prusa printers, and the `A` parameter sets the object name. This indicates that the printer will be printing embossed text onto the object.\r\n\r\nThe output has been written to `/app/out.txt`.\r\n"]
[100.805673, "o", "\u001b[?2004hroot@8a477b961aa2:/app# "]
